-- RBC Hires Stanicky, Francis to Expand in U.S. Health Care
-- B y   D o u g   A l e x a n d e r
-- 2013-11-12T16:53:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-11-12/rbc-hires-stanicky-francis-to-expand-in-u-s-health-care.html
Royal Bank of Canada , the country’s
largest lender, hired  Randall Stanicky  and David Francis as
managing directors to expand coverage of U.S. health-care
companies at its investment bank.  Stanicky joined in  New York  as lead analyst for the
specialty and generic pharmaceuticals group of  RBC Capital
Markets , the Toronto-based firm said today in an e-mailed
statement. Stanicky has 14 years of experience, and previously
covered health care for  Canaccord Genuity Group Inc. (CF) , Goldman
Sachs Group Inc. and Citigroup Global Asset Management.  Francis, a former managing director at Jefferies Group LLC,
joined RBC’s Nashville, Tennessee, office, where he covers
health-care information technology and distribution services,
the company said. Francis, who has more than 20 years of
experience, was last at JAAG Group, a research and advisory firm
where he was founder and managing partner.  To contact the reporter on this story:
